\begin_layout Section*
Resources and competetive position
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
One possibility is to view the competetive strength of DICE as resting on
 the quality of the technogical base (resources), which in turn depends
 on the processes, and the people who implement them - an inside-out view.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Another view is to consider the competitive strength of the products as
 a result of accurate intepretation of customer demand, and to view the
 technological base as the inevitable investment necessary to realize the
 end product.
 The tech base (production resources) is then a by-product of product strategy.
 This would be an outside-in view.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There is merit in both these views depending on time-perspective, but I
 think the latter closer to truth in the case of DICE and a much more useful
 conclusion.
\end_layout

